com.pedroalmir.athena.core.algorithm
Class AbstractAlgorithm

java.lang.Object
  com.pedroalmir.athena.core.algorithm.AbstractAlgorithm
All Implemented Interfaces:
Algorithm, ConfigurableAlgorithm, Stoppable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Runnable
Direct Known Subclasses:
FuzzyAlgorithm, NSGAIIAlgorithm
public abstract class AbstractAlgorithm
extends java.lang.Object
implements Algorithm, Stoppable, ConfigurableAlgorithm

All algorithms in Athena should be subclasses of Algorithm. This class handles stopping criteria, events, threading and measurements.

Subclasses of Algorithm must provide an implementation for Algorithm.performIteration(). If a subclass overrides algorithmInitialisation() then it must call super.initialise().
